---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Documentation - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen p-8 py-16 doc-page">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
          Documentation
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--text-muted)]">
          Everything you need to get started with Helpmaton
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Related resources -->
        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Related resources
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Quick links to other helpful pages.
          </p>
          <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
            <li>
              <a href="/faq" class="doc-link font-medium">
                FAQ
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/getting-started" class="doc-link font-medium">
                Getting Started
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://app.helpmaton.com/docs/api" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="doc-link font-medium">
                API Reference
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/blog" class="doc-link font-medium">
                Blog
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Prominent FAQ Link -->
        <section
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-neon-cyan/20 to-neon-magenta/20 rounded-xl p-8 border border-neon-cyan/30 shadow-neon-cyan text-[var(--text-primary)]"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="text-4xl">❓</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">
                Quick Answers to Common Questions
              </h2>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-4 text-lg">
                Looking for quick answers? Our FAQ covers setup, agents, workspaces, billing, and more.
              </p>
              <a
                href="/faq"
                class="doc-cta inline-block px-6 py-3 font-semibold rounded-lg transition-all"
              >
                View FAQ →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Getting Started
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            New to Helpmaton? Start here. We'll guide you through creating your
            first workspace, setting up agents, and uploading documents.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/getting-started"
            class="doc-cta inline-block px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm transition-all"
          >
            Read Getting Started Guide →
          </a>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Working with Agents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Learn how to create and manage your AI agents, from basic setup to
            more advanced options.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating your first agent</li>
            <li>Setting agent tone and instructions</li>
            <li>Enabling tools and integrations</li>
            <li>Scheduling recurring work</li>
            <li>Delegating tasks to other agents</li>
            <li>Reviewing quality with evals</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Evaluation & Quality Control (Judge Evals)
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Use judge evaluations to score conversations, validate outcomes, and
            catch regressions after you change prompts, tools, or integrations.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Run evals with just a couple of clicks</li>
            <li>Score outcomes and track quality over time</li>
            <li>Use sampling to balance insight and cost</li>
            <li>Validate behavior before shipping changes</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Agent Memory System
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Agents remember key details from conversations so they can respond
            with more helpful context.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Memory grouped by time periods</li>
            <li>Summaries created over time (daily, weekly, monthly, etc.)</li>
            <li>Custom summarization prompts per agent and time grain</li>
            <li>Smart search to find past details</li>
            <li>
              Memory length depends on your plan (Free: 48h + 30d summaries,
              Pro: 240h + 120d)
            </li>
            <li>Automatic cleanup to save space</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Workspaces
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Organize your AI agents into workspaces. Each workspace is a
            separate space with its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <div
            class="mb-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Workspace credits cover AI provider usage,
              not your Helpmaton subscription. You can use your own API keys or
              buy credits through Helpmaton.
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating and managing workspaces</li>
            <li>Setting spending limits for AI usage</li>
            <li>Agent-specific limits with daily, monthly, or yearly caps</li>
            <li>Using your own API keys or buying credits</li>
            <li>
              Team collaboration and shared access (Pro plans support unlimited
              managers)
            </li>
            <li>Workspace permissions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Documents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Upload and organize documents so your agents can use them as a
            knowledge base.
          </p>
          <div
            class="mb-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
              <strong>Document formats:</strong> Knowledge base documents support
              <strong>Markdown and text</strong>. For other file types and
              images, use <strong>conversation attachments</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Uploading documents</li>
            <li>Organizing with folders</li>
            <li>Supported formats: Markdown + text</li>
            <li>Document management tips</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Conversation Attachments
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Attach files and images directly to a conversation to give your
            agent richer context for troubleshooting, review, and multi-modal
            workflows.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Attach files and images while chatting</li>
            <li>Great for screenshots, reports, and file reviews</li>
            <li>Different from knowledge base documents</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Usage Analytics & Monitoring
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Track usage so you can understand and manage your AI spending. View
            clear reports across your work.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Usage tracking for all AI requests</li>
            <li>Daily and hourly summaries</li>
            <li>History by date range</li>
            <li>Breakdowns by workspace and agent</li>
            <li>Cost tracking and budget checks</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Web Search & Content Extraction
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Give your agents access to up-to-date information. Enable web search
            and content extraction so they can look things up and summarize
            pages.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Web Search
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can search the web for current information, news, and
                research. Results include titles, links, and short summaries.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Find current information</li>
                <li>Answer questions about recent events</li>
                <li>Discover new articles and resources</li>
                <li>Support research and monitoring</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Content Extraction
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Give a URL and the agent will read and summarize that page.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Extract the main content</li>
                <li>Summarize articles and resources</li>
                <li>Pull key points from pages</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Pricing</h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                All plans include a daily allowance, with low-cost pay-as-you-go
                pricing after that.
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Turn on web search and content extraction per agent in settings.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-3">
            Web search and content extraction help your agents provide current
            information when you need it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Webhooks & Integrations
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect Helpmaton to your tools and workflows. Set up webhooks and
            automate common tasks.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Setting up webhooks</li>
            <li>Real-time updates</li>
            <li>Streaming responses (SSE) for chat-like experiences</li>
            <li>Webhook events and payloads</li>
            <li>Integration examples</li>
            <li>Troubleshooting</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Agent Schedules
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Automate agent runs with cron-based schedules. Perfect for recurring
            reports, proactive monitoring, and routine operational tasks.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Run agents on a schedule with cron expressions</li>
            <li>Send results to email or notification channels</li>
            <li>Combine schedules with web search and integrations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Built-in Tools & External Integrations
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Agents come with built-in tools and can connect to external services
            when you need more.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Built-in Tools
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Every agent has access to these tools:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>Document Search:</strong> Find information in your
                  documents
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Memory Search:</strong> Recall past conversations and
                  details
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Web Search:</strong> Look up current information and
                  articles
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Web Fetch:</strong> Read and summarize a web page
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Email Sending:</strong> Send emails from your workspace
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Notification Sending:</strong> Send updates to Discord
                  or Slack
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Agent Delegation:</strong> Pass tasks to other agents
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                External Integrations (Extensibility)
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Extend your agents with external integrations (MCP servers), like
                APIs, databases, and custom tools.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>What external integrations are</li>
                <li>Setting up connections with authentication</li>
                <li>Enabling integrations per agent</li>
                <li>Security basics</li>
                <li>Use cases and examples</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Google Workspace Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect Gmail, Google Calendar, and Google Drive in a few clicks. No
            complex setup needed. Your agents can manage your calendar, read and
            search emails, and access Drive files.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Easy Secure Sign-In
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Setting it up is simple and secure:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
                <li>Create a connection for Gmail, Calendar, or Drive</li>
                <li>Click "Connect Google Account" and sign in</li>
                <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
                <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)]">
                All connections use secure sign-in to keep your data private.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Gmail Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Connect agents to Gmail so they can:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>List and search emails</li>
                <li>Read full email content and attachments</li>
                <li>Use Gmail search filters</li>
                <li>Support inbox management and follow-ups</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Google Calendar Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Connect agents to Google Calendar to:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>List events and search</li>
                <li>Read event details</li>
                <li>Create and update events</li>
                <li>Delete events when needed</li>
                <li>Support scheduling and meeting coordination</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Google Drive Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Give agents access to files stored in Google Drive:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Read text files and documents</li>
                <li>Access Google Docs (as plain text)</li>
                <li>Read Google Sheets (as CSV)</li>
                <li>Access Google Slides (as plain text)</li>
                <li>Great for document review and data checks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-3">
            Google Workspace integrations let agents work with your Google
            services. See the <a href="https://github.com/djinilabs/helpmaton/blob/main/docs/mcp-servers.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="doc-link underline">MCP Servers documentation</a> for setup details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Notion Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect Notion in a few clicks. Your agents can read and search
            pages, create and update content, and work with databases.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Easy Secure Sign-In
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Setting it up is simple and secure:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
                <li>Create a connection and select "Notion"</li>
                <li>Click "Connect Notion Account" and sign in</li>
                <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
                <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)]">
                All connections use secure sign-in to keep your data private.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Page Management
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can read, search, create, and update Notion pages:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Read pages, including properties and content</li>
                <li>Search pages and databases</li>
                <li>Create new pages with content</li>
                <li>Update page properties and content</li>
                <li>Add blocks like paragraphs, headings, and lists</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Database Management
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can query and manage Notion databases:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Filter and sort records</li>
                <li>Create new entries with properties</li>
                <li>Update existing entries</li>
                <li>Great for knowledge and project tracking</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-3">
            Notion integration helps agents work with your workspace for docs and
            knowledge bases. See the <a href="https://github.com/djinilabs/helpmaton/blob/main/docs/mcp-servers.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="doc-link underline">MCP Servers documentation</a> for setup instructions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Error Tracking
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Conversations are saved and errors are shown when something fails,
            making issues easy to spot and fix.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Errors saved in conversations</li>
            <li>Clear error messages</li>
            <li>Provider details when available</li>
            <li>Error badges for quick spotting</li>
            <li>Full context when you open an error</li>
            <li>History across conversations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Error tracking works automatically. When requests fail, errors show
            up right away.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Agent Delegation
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Agents can pass tasks to other agents in the same workspace, so work
            gets shared.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>How agent delegation works</li>
            <li>Setting up multi-agent workflows</li>
            <li>Sharing tasks and coordinating work</li>
            <li>Specialized agent teams</li>
            <li>Use cases for collaboration</li>
            <li>Best practices for delegation</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Agent delegation lets you build teams where each agent handles the
            part they’re best at.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="doc-card rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
            Email Sending
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Set up email access so agents can send emails from your workspace.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Setting up workspace email connections</li>
            <li>Adding email authentication</li>
            <li>Using email tools in agents</li>
            <li>Email templates and formatting</li>
            <li>Best practices for email replies</li>
          </ul>
